WEBVTT

00:06.310 --> 00:07.659
You guys are good?

00:07.703 --> 00:08.791
Awesome.

00:08.834 --> 00:10.401
Oh.

00:11.359 --> 00:12.490
We're rolling.

00:12.534 --> 00:14.318
What I've done
for the last 20 years

00:14.362 --> 00:16.494
is direct response marketing.

00:16.538 --> 00:19.280
I make... millions.

00:19.323 --> 00:21.282
Hey, you gotta do what you gotta
do for money.

00:21.325 --> 00:23.327
I'm like the Wizard of Oz.

00:23.371 --> 00:27.505
Lisa and I met the first
Sundance that I lived in Utah.

00:27.549 --> 00:30.334
I know she has my back. I know
she wants what's best for me.

00:30.378 --> 00:33.076
I know there's
no ulterior motive there.

00:33.120 --> 00:36.645
She was like, "Oh, my God.
You're amazing,"

00:36.688 --> 00:38.516
and I just felt
the same way about her.

00:38.560 --> 00:42.564
I just really like that Meredith
is 100% Meredith all the time.

00:42.607 --> 00:45.306
She's super consistent,
and she's a great person.

00:45.349 --> 00:47.830
Heather and I have been friends
for years.

00:47.873 --> 00:50.920
We are actually cousins.
We are bloodline relatives.

00:50.963 --> 00:52.182
She's the best human I know,

00:52.226 --> 00:54.706
and she's such a good friend
to me.

00:54.750 --> 00:57.405
She never explodes on me.
I can tell her anything I want,

00:57.448 --> 01:00.408
critical or otherwise, and I
know that she will listen,

01:00.451 --> 01:02.627
and we can talk it out.

01:06.936 --> 01:08.459
Our time is coming.

01:08.503 --> 01:11.723
I just can't lie to you.
This is a test for all of us.

01:13.160 --> 01:15.249
I wanna----ing kill myself.

01:15.292 --> 01:16.380
Jen, you know what? Right now--

01:16.424 --> 01:18.556
And just not be here.

01:18.600 --> 01:21.255
Everything's been taken away
from me!

01:21.298 --> 01:22.604
Everything!

01:24.214 --> 01:25.476
- Confide in you, Lisa.
- You haven't.

01:25.520 --> 01:27.652
'Cause I never
fully trusted you.

01:27.696 --> 01:29.306
I was talking to myself!

01:29.350 --> 01:31.569
I was ranting
like normal people do!

01:31.613 --> 01:33.136
- To speak about your...
- Yeah.

01:33.180 --> 01:35.878
...dear friend that way. Okay.

01:35.921 --> 01:37.488
- You are my girl, Heather.
- Is it possible you're wrong...

01:37.532 --> 01:39.142
- No. No.
- ...and making it all about you?

01:39.186 --> 01:40.752
No.

01:40.796 --> 01:43.407
Show up for your people.

01:43.451 --> 01:46.193
You are saying our friendship
is bullsh--.

01:46.236 --> 01:48.934
That----ing hurts me, Heather.

01:48.978 --> 01:52.895
you for calling me
a----ing liar!

01:52.938 --> 01:54.592
You called me a liar.

01:54.636 --> 01:57.334
You lost <i>me,</i> bitch.
You lost me.

02:01.469 --> 02:03.775
But what people don't know
about Salt Lake City

02:03.819 --> 02:06.952
is what lies beneath
that image of perfection.

02:06.996 --> 02:08.563
Let me say that again.

02:10.478 --> 02:13.307
This is so unnerving. Okay.

02:46.340 --> 02:48.168
- Hey, John.
- Oh, you look great.

02:48.211 --> 02:50.170
Thanks. Um, I'm gonna head out.

02:50.213 --> 02:51.736
I'm gonna head to lunch
right now.

02:51.780 --> 02:54.304
Oh, yeah?
How you feeling about it?

02:54.348 --> 02:56.001
Um, I'll let you know
when I'm done.

02:56.045 --> 02:58.482
- Okay. Looking forward to it.
- Okay, love you.

02:58.526 --> 03:00.267
All right, love you.

03:04.271 --> 03:06.055
<i>Hello?</i>

03:06.098 --> 03:07.535
Hi. How are you?

03:07.578 --> 03:09.624
<i>Good. I just got out
of a meeting. How are you?</i>

03:09.667 --> 03:14.672
Oh, I'm good. I'm actually on
my way to, um, meet someone.

03:14.716 --> 03:16.805
I'll probably be, like,
a little unreachable

03:16.848 --> 03:19.024
for a few hours.

03:26.728 --> 03:28.773
Well, hello.

03:28.817 --> 03:30.732
You were literally
around the corner.

03:30.775 --> 03:32.995
- I wasn't kidding.
- No.

03:33.038 --> 03:35.215
You look cute.

03:35.258 --> 03:36.955
Oh, I love it.

03:38.348 --> 03:40.176
- Hey, Heather.
- Hi.

03:40.220 --> 03:41.786
- How are you?
- Good. How are you?

03:41.830 --> 03:44.354
- Good to see you.
- It's good to see you.

03:46.487 --> 03:50.186
- This is beautiful.
- Isn't it nice?

03:50.230 --> 03:54.103
Oh, my gosh.
What a gorgeous view.

03:54.146 --> 03:57.062
Not too chilly, and the hot tub
will feel nice and warm.

03:58.716 --> 04:02.154
Okay.
Put our stuff in a locker.

04:02.198 --> 04:03.591
If someone asked me
eight months ago

04:03.634 --> 04:06.681
if I'd be hanging out
with Jen...

04:06.724 --> 04:09.727
I would look at them
like they were crazy.

04:09.771 --> 04:11.773
Did you like a comment
referring to my son

04:11.816 --> 04:12.861
as a sissy bitch?

04:12.904 --> 04:16.604
- No!
- It's your----ing Twitter, Jen!

04:18.475 --> 04:20.129
Miracles do happen.

04:20.172 --> 04:23.132
Oh, this looks so pretty.
I can't wait to get in.

04:23.175 --> 04:24.699
This looks phenomenal.

04:24.742 --> 04:27.005
When Jen and I were in L.A.,

04:27.049 --> 04:29.399
I think that she sort of
got an understanding

04:29.443 --> 04:31.749
of everything that
I went through last winter.

04:31.793 --> 04:33.577
I had some very serious issues

04:33.621 --> 04:35.275
well beyond just losing
my father.

04:35.318 --> 04:41.933
My reactions, everything was
amplified a million times over.

04:41.977 --> 04:43.718
I totally understand,
and, Meredith, honestly,

04:43.761 --> 04:48.592
when I saw you,
I saw myself a year ago.

04:48.636 --> 04:50.420
Thank you.

04:50.464 --> 04:54.511
Cheers. Here's to a new year
and a new us.

04:54.555 --> 04:56.470
I will drink to that.

04:56.513 --> 04:58.820
No more fighting.

05:00.387 --> 05:02.432
It's just all love
from here on out.

05:02.476 --> 05:05.609
Yeah. It was--
It was a tough winter

05:05.653 --> 05:07.655
for both of us, you know?

05:07.698 --> 05:09.439
Yeah. What are you feeling
right now

05:09.483 --> 05:13.835
after Lisa going on her tirade?

05:20.102 --> 05:22.365
- I felt that.
- It's a process, and I mean,

05:22.409 --> 05:24.454
I'm still dealing with it
in a lot of ways.

05:24.498 --> 05:26.630
- Oh, yeah.
- And I'm sure I will be

05:26.674 --> 05:28.153
for a while, you know?
- Yeah.

05:28.197 --> 05:30.155
I've been going through so much,
and you know,

05:30.199 --> 05:33.420
my trial starts in, like,
a month and a half.

05:38.990 --> 05:41.515
And so I'm trying to plan

05:41.558 --> 05:44.300
a birthday party
for Coach Shah,

05:44.344 --> 05:47.129
just to show Coach I--
how much I appreciate him.

05:47.172 --> 05:51.916
And so I was planning
on inviting Lisa and John.

05:51.960 --> 05:54.615
How's everything going?

05:54.658 --> 05:56.312
- I mean, good.
- Here's a water for you.

05:56.356 --> 05:59.141
She's gonna--She's gonna take
a Vida Paloma, too.

05:59.184 --> 06:00.708
- Excellent. Would you like poco?
- I ordered for you.

06:00.751 --> 06:04.755
Yeah, I-I trust Lisa explicitly
with alcohol, so...

06:04.799 --> 06:08.759
I agreed to meet with Lisa
because she said she needed me,

06:08.803 --> 06:11.240
and she's never said
she's needed me before.

06:11.283 --> 06:12.502
I never called Heather Shrek.

06:12.546 --> 06:14.025
Oh, you've called me
horrible things, Lisa.

06:14.069 --> 06:15.418
I have never called you Shrek.
I have never--

06:15.462 --> 06:18.029
You've called me
a LEGO figurine.

06:18.073 --> 06:19.640
The fact that she's scraping
the bottom of the barrel

06:19.683 --> 06:21.468
to call me, the--probably
the last person on the earth

06:21.511 --> 06:23.034
that she wants to call?

06:23.078 --> 06:27.082
If I can do something
of value for Lisa,

06:27.125 --> 06:31.478
then maybe she won't hate me
as much.

06:31.521 --> 06:33.567
To us.

06:33.610 --> 06:35.395
To us.
I didn't expect that, but okay.

06:35.438 --> 06:37.788
For me, it's, like,
very uncomfortable to say this,

06:37.832 --> 06:41.401
but, like, I need some help
with Meredith.

06:41.444 --> 06:44.055
I feel like you are able to
navigate situations differently.

06:44.099 --> 06:45.622
Like, I feel like you say
what you're thinking,

06:45.666 --> 06:47.015
you say what you're feeling.

06:47.058 --> 06:49.278
And you, like,
end up, like, fine,

06:49.321 --> 06:53.238
and I feel like now, I'm like,
like the worst person on earth,

06:53.282 --> 06:55.327
in, like, Meredith's eyes.
- Like you've been banished.

06:55.371 --> 06:56.154
I need your advice.
I need help.

06:56.198 --> 06:57.678
Well...

06:57.721 --> 07:00.463
What is most sacred to Meredith?
If I were to ask you,

07:00.507 --> 07:01.856
without any influence--
- Her family.

07:01.899 --> 07:03.031
- Okay.
- Yeah. Her family.

07:03.074 --> 07:05.207
Yeah. And you came
for her family?

07:05.250 --> 07:06.774
I didn't feel like
I came for her family.

07:06.817 --> 07:08.340
I was in a blind rage.
It wasn't intentional.

07:08.384 --> 07:09.603
- Listen...
- I get it.

07:09.646 --> 07:11.387
Regardless, it's on the table.
You did.

07:11.431 --> 07:13.171
So you have to make it right.

07:13.215 --> 07:15.173
The questions that are gonna be
asked are

07:15.217 --> 07:18.176
is that how you really feel
about Meredith?

07:18.220 --> 07:20.265
What do you think?

07:20.309 --> 07:22.485
I think that's how you really
feel about Meredith.

07:22.529 --> 07:24.792
No. No. No. No.

07:24.835 --> 07:26.358
I don't know.
I'm still trying to figure out

07:26.402 --> 07:28.665
where I stand on everything.

07:28.709 --> 07:30.450
I mean, she went through

07:30.493 --> 07:32.452
and completely defamed
my character

07:32.495 --> 07:34.454
on things that just aren't true.

07:37.674 --> 07:40.416
And so then you say,
"Well, where did this come from?

07:40.460 --> 07:43.114
Are you listening to rumors
and spreading rumors?

07:43.158 --> 07:45.116
Because at the end of the day,
I'm hearing rumors

07:45.160 --> 07:47.162
left, right, and center.
- About Lisa?

07:47.205 --> 07:51.427
About Lisa.
And am I spreading them? No.

07:51.471 --> 07:55.953
So let's see. Is it--Is it just
her projecting her own truth,

07:55.997 --> 07:59.479
or is it just she decided to be
a total asshole

07:59.522 --> 08:01.350
'cause she was angry?

08:01.393 --> 08:07.182
The sh-- Lisa Barlow said about
her "sister" and best friend?

08:07.225 --> 08:10.968
What Meredith needs to do is
monetize that.

08:11.012 --> 08:14.711
Make "Garbage trash whore"
T-shirts.

08:14.755 --> 08:17.453
So what rumors are you hearing?

08:18.541 --> 08:21.718
Um...

08:21.762 --> 08:23.938
There have been question marks
surrounding her marriage,

08:23.981 --> 08:27.942
um... her business
and her finances.

08:27.985 --> 08:29.813
Do I really wanna dig
into Lisa's stuff?

08:29.857 --> 08:31.423
No, I really have no interest.

08:31.467 --> 08:33.643
But if you're going to sit there
talking about everyone else,

08:33.687 --> 08:35.906
fair game on her at this point.

08:35.950 --> 08:38.561
Fair game.

08:38.605 --> 08:40.520
I mean, there are--
there are affair rumors.

08:40.563 --> 08:42.565
I'm not getting into any of it,
but there are rumors.

08:42.609 --> 08:45.307
I don't know
if they're true or false.

08:45.350 --> 08:46.569
Um... but the exist.

08:46.613 --> 08:48.528
Yeah, I've heard the same thing.

08:50.051 --> 08:52.227
Even if you feel like
what you said is justified,

08:52.270 --> 08:54.055
if you feel like what you said--

08:54.098 --> 08:55.752
I didn't feel like it was
justified, just so--

08:55.796 --> 08:57.188
I mean, we have to be clear
about that.

08:57.232 --> 08:59.060
- I'm very clear about that.
- It doesn't even matter.

08:59.103 --> 09:00.670
It's like,
you're in the position

09:00.714 --> 09:02.367
where you have to say,
"I didn't mean it.

09:02.411 --> 09:05.022
It was a moment, and I'm going
to have to eat sh-- for it

09:05.066 --> 09:06.894
for a long time."

09:06.937 --> 09:09.984
I don't think humble pie
is something that Lisa

09:10.027 --> 09:13.291
likes to eat, will ever eat,

09:13.335 --> 09:17.382
or will for sure never pretend
to enjoy eating.

09:17.426 --> 09:19.776
And all three of those things
need to occur

09:19.820 --> 09:21.691
for her to bridge this gap
with Meredith.

09:21.735 --> 09:23.519
I've eaten so much humble pie,

09:23.563 --> 09:25.739
it's amazing I still fit
in this dress.

09:25.782 --> 09:28.959
I think there needs to be give
on both sides, honestly.

09:29.003 --> 09:31.353
But the bigger side
has to come from you.

09:31.396 --> 09:32.702
- Okay.
- Because you said

09:32.746 --> 09:36.880
the mean things
that are out there forever.

09:36.924 --> 09:41.058
Okay, I hear you. I hear you.

09:46.455 --> 09:47.891
<i>Coming up...</i>

09:47.935 --> 09:49.545
If you say to the Church,

09:49.589 --> 09:51.242
"I want you
to ex-communicate me.

09:51.286 --> 09:52.722
I want to remove my name
from the records,"

09:52.766 --> 09:56.291
what changes
in your day-to-day life?

10:06.954 --> 10:08.825
What's up, Bobbie Rose?

10:11.698 --> 10:13.525
Wait, what?

10:13.569 --> 10:15.963
Pros and cons about guys?

10:16.006 --> 10:17.791
- Yes!
- What do you mean by guys?

10:17.834 --> 10:20.750
- Like, men.
- Like, <i>men?</i>

10:20.794 --> 10:22.143
Yes.

10:22.186 --> 10:23.579
How old are you, Bobbi Rose?

10:23.623 --> 10:25.799
Let me see what you got. Pros...

10:25.842 --> 10:27.888
Athletic.

10:27.931 --> 10:29.150
- Good style.
- Nice.

10:29.193 --> 10:32.022
- That's a big one. Hi, Dad.
- Hey.

10:32.066 --> 10:33.589
Dad, come look at this.

10:33.633 --> 10:35.286
She's writing
a pros and cons list about guys.

10:35.330 --> 10:37.680
You're gonna take that one up
with your daddy.

10:37.724 --> 10:39.160
Well, I'm really worried

10:39.203 --> 10:41.989
that there's not as many cons
as there are pros.

10:42.032 --> 10:43.817
I don't know how I feel
about that.

10:43.860 --> 10:45.688
Whit?

10:45.732 --> 10:46.994
- Hello!
- Hey!

10:47.037 --> 10:49.779
Get in here.
I need a rescue right now.

10:49.823 --> 10:50.954
- Hi.
- Hi.

10:50.998 --> 10:52.434
- You need a rescue?
- Yes, I need--

10:52.477 --> 10:53.522
What's going on?

10:53.565 --> 10:54.436
I need--I need you
to tag in here.

10:54.479 --> 10:56.568
- Hi, Bobbie.
- Hi.

10:56.612 --> 10:57.874
This is a department
I don't know much about.

10:57.918 --> 10:59.571
What's up?
What are we working on?

10:59.615 --> 11:01.095
Pros and cons about guys.

11:01.138 --> 11:02.792
Well, it's gonna be hard
to get any cons from me, Bobbie.

11:04.272 --> 11:06.622
She's completely
and utterly boy-crazy.

11:06.666 --> 11:08.972
Sixth grade.
Like, think of sixth grade.

11:09.016 --> 11:11.366
I didn't have my first kiss
till 15.

11:11.409 --> 11:12.672
That's too long!

11:12.715 --> 11:14.412
I didn't have my first kiss
till 15 either.

11:14.456 --> 11:15.587
Oh, my gosh. Okay.

11:15.631 --> 11:17.372
But I still wanted it
in sixth grade.

11:18.329 --> 11:19.809
I was a good little Mormon girl,

11:19.853 --> 11:21.550
and I followed all the rules.

11:21.593 --> 11:23.160
I was not interested in boys

11:23.204 --> 11:26.076
until the Mormon Handbook
told me I could be.

11:26.120 --> 11:28.818
I just put,
"Doesn't do what's asked of me,"

11:28.862 --> 11:30.298
so I think they don't listen
to me.

11:30.341 --> 11:32.822
Honey, you gotta take that
off your list.

11:32.866 --> 11:34.519
You don't want someone

11:34.563 --> 11:37.348
that does exactly what
you ask them to do all the time.

11:37.392 --> 11:40.351
Bobbie Rose has some
ridiculously high standards.

11:40.395 --> 11:42.702
I think you can dress a guy.
I don't think style matters.

11:42.745 --> 11:44.181
Oh, yeah. That is true.

11:44.225 --> 11:45.792
I just wanna take, like,
a Sharpie

11:45.835 --> 11:47.358
and just be like,
"Never gonna get it.

11:47.402 --> 11:49.143
Never gonna get it.
Never gonna get it.

11:49.186 --> 11:50.840
Settle. Settle. Settle."

11:50.884 --> 11:53.016
Not attractive. Ugly sex--
it's gonna change your life.

11:53.060 --> 11:54.757
Let's switch that one over, too.

11:57.281 --> 11:59.196
I want to be as hopeful
as Bobbie Rose

11:59.240 --> 12:01.808
when I make out
my pros and cons list, honestly.

12:01.851 --> 12:04.375
- Let's go downstairs.
- What can I get you to drink?

12:04.419 --> 12:06.377
Whatever you guys are drinking.

12:06.421 --> 12:09.554
There's rosé
or a really nice tequila.

12:09.598 --> 12:14.168
You know what? In a nod to me
being Team Lisa Barlow lately,

12:14.211 --> 12:15.560
let's do a tequila.

12:15.604 --> 12:16.910
All right. Got you.

12:19.782 --> 12:21.392
- Hi. <i>
- Hi. [laughs]</i>

12:21.436 --> 12:23.046
<i>I need to talk to you.
I'm dying.</i>

12:23.090 --> 12:24.961
What's going on?

12:25.005 --> 12:26.920
<i>I'm on my way to meet up
with Lisa.</i>

12:28.704 --> 12:32.186
It's good. As much as I wanna
be like, "No! Run,"

12:32.229 --> 12:33.796
we need to get over our sh--.

12:35.929 --> 12:38.061
- When did you do this?
- Yeah, we made it a speakeasy.

12:38.105 --> 12:39.149
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

12:39.193 --> 12:40.542
And you can lock
the bookshelves.

12:40.585 --> 12:42.196
- It has the lock up top.
- Oh, my gosh.

12:42.239 --> 12:45.590
This is so cool...
you guys. Yes!

12:45.634 --> 12:47.418
Feels good to me, too.

12:47.462 --> 12:49.246
I love it, and, like,
close the door, padlock it,

12:49.290 --> 12:50.900
don't let the kids in.

12:50.944 --> 12:52.815
The fact that we have a bar
in our home is a big deal.

12:52.859 --> 12:55.426
I never knew anyone with a bar.

12:55.470 --> 12:57.733
I remember, like,
going to my friend's house,

12:57.777 --> 12:59.866
and, like, seeing her parents,
like, drinking wine,

12:59.909 --> 13:02.520
and being like, "OMG."

13:04.087 --> 13:06.698
But, no, I, um, you know
I've been, like, on this, like,

13:06.742 --> 13:09.571
healing journey,
and I had a big healing session

13:09.614 --> 13:11.268
with Megan the other day.

13:11.312 --> 13:14.445
So the past keeps showing up
over and over.

13:14.489 --> 13:16.273
'Cause I don't have a memory
of it.

13:16.317 --> 13:18.885
Yeah, and I think that's what's
manifesting in your gut.

13:18.928 --> 13:20.190
It's wanting to stay
in the past,

13:20.234 --> 13:22.889
trying to resolve
what happened in the past.

13:22.932 --> 13:25.021
The great thing
about this trauma

13:25.065 --> 13:28.720
with your early childhood is
clearing out this old energy

13:28.764 --> 13:30.679
allows you to move forward.

13:30.722 --> 13:33.682
This energy we're gonna hand
to the universe.

13:33.725 --> 13:35.945
Up and over your body.

13:35.989 --> 13:37.468
Think of this trauma.

13:37.512 --> 13:39.906
Ask yourself,
"Is it still here?"

13:39.949 --> 13:42.778
- Can I hug you?
- Yes, please do.

13:42.822 --> 13:46.173
And it really hit me that
one of the biggest tethers

13:46.216 --> 13:50.438
or, like, wounds I have
is the Church.

13:50.481 --> 13:55.660
And I came to the realization
that I'm ready

13:55.704 --> 13:58.968
to close that chapter
and leave officially

13:59.012 --> 14:01.536
