a good time.

33:15.297 --> 33:16.516
- Man, Mama.
- You never relax.

33:16.559 --> 33:18.387
- I know, huh?
- All right, go, boy.

33:18.431 --> 33:19.693
- Do your thang.
- Come on, you wanna get

33:19.736 --> 33:22.087
a little something to sip on?
- Oh.

33:24.654 --> 33:27.222
- Everybody!
- Come on.

33:27.266 --> 33:28.441
- Whoo!
- Shh!

33:28.484 --> 33:31.270
- We need Jen to make a speech.
- Shh!

33:31.313 --> 33:34.229
Everybody, we need Jen to make

33:34.273 --> 33:36.492
a little toast
to the birthday boy.

33:36.536 --> 33:38.233
Coach doesn't really like

33:38.277 --> 33:39.539
celebrating his birthday
that much.

33:39.582 --> 33:41.236
I don't.

33:41.280 --> 33:45.371
But, you know, this year
was very special.

33:45.414 --> 33:48.809
It was important for me
to show you

33:48.852 --> 33:51.290
how much I love
and appreciate you.

33:51.333 --> 33:54.293
I know we've been through a lot.

33:54.336 --> 33:58.166
And, um...

33:58.210 --> 34:00.647
because of everything
we've been going through,

34:00.690 --> 34:03.693
it means more to me than ever

34:03.737 --> 34:06.957
in my life to have people
that I know...

34:07.001 --> 34:08.481
that really, truly love me

34:08.524 --> 34:10.091
and love our family.

34:10.135 --> 34:11.223
- We love you, Jen!
- MAN #2: We love you, baby!

34:14.356 --> 34:16.010
- That's right!
- Always.

34:16.054 --> 34:17.751
And to everybody that
has been there and just...

34:17.794 --> 34:20.710
thank you for being here
to wish Coach a happy birthday,

34:20.754 --> 34:23.191
because this birthday, I think,
means more to me

34:23.235 --> 34:25.802
than anything because we can
still be here together

34:25.846 --> 34:26.977
to celebrate it.

34:27.021 --> 34:28.631
I know that's right!

34:28.675 --> 34:30.416
Amen.

34:30.459 --> 34:32.983
And, Angie and Shawn,
thank you so much.

34:33.027 --> 34:35.247
Thank you for opening up
your home,

34:35.290 --> 34:37.727
and for celebrating with us.

34:37.771 --> 34:40.730
The one thing that can bring me
to tears almost instantly

34:40.774 --> 34:46.867
is thinking of life
without my wife by my side.

34:46.910 --> 34:50.653
That's hard to...
it's hard to stomach.

34:50.697 --> 34:51.567
Make a wish, baby.

35:17.419 --> 35:19.465
- Yeah.
- I'm doing good.

35:19.508 --> 35:21.989
Good to see you, man.

35:22.032 --> 35:24.470
- Are you in town long?
- This week,

35:24.513 --> 35:26.907
but, yeah. Yeah.

35:26.950 --> 35:31.085
Well, if you can break away,
let me know.

35:31.129 --> 35:34.088
Yeah. It's, uh...

35:38.179 --> 35:42.096
It... whatever our wives are--
I hope that's...

35:42.140 --> 35:42.966
Yes.

35:48.450 --> 35:49.669
Our relationship--

35:49.712 --> 35:51.105
I'm not accountable
for Meredith's behavior.

35:51.149 --> 35:54.674
I know you're not accountable
for Lisa's behavior.

35:54.717 --> 35:56.110
- I have to believe that...
- Yes.

35:56.154 --> 35:57.720
...'cause I know it's true
for me.

35:57.764 --> 36:01.594
Oh, for sure. For sure.
No, that'll never change.

36:01.637 --> 36:03.204
- Yeah.
- Never change at all.

36:03.248 --> 36:04.684
I do like your tie.

36:04.727 --> 36:07.861
Thank you, man.
You look sharp. Looking good.

36:07.904 --> 36:10.646
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

36:10.690 --> 36:13.562
<i>♪ Hit it, Rico, hit it, Rico</i>

36:13.606 --> 36:16.043
<i>Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey!</i>

36:16.086 --> 36:18.698
<i>♪ Hit it, Rico, hit it, Rico</i>

36:18.741 --> 36:20.830
- Aah!
- Whoo!

36:24.051 --> 36:27.272
<i>-♪ Hit it, Rico, hit it Rico</i>
- Oh, there you go.

36:34.061 --> 36:37.195
You better slow down, baby!
You know you gotta slow down!

36:37.238 --> 36:38.935
Well, you do know that.

36:38.979 --> 36:40.241
- Hey.
- Hi! Oh, my gosh.

36:40.285 --> 36:42.896
What if I have a King?
What if I have a King?

36:42.939 --> 36:44.463
Yeah, a King for a Queen.
A King for a Queen.

36:44.506 --> 36:46.421
I love it.

36:46.465 --> 36:48.597
I'm gonna pinch you some chips.
How are you doing?

36:48.641 --> 36:50.991
- How's your night?
- Good. Oh, my gosh. Good.

36:51.034 --> 36:54.603
Are you gonna say anything
to Meredith or Seth?

36:54.647 --> 36:56.866
I don't think the time's right
right now.

36:58.041 --> 36:59.782
I just don't think
it's the right time.

36:59.826 --> 37:00.957
Time's not about that.
You know what I mean?

37:01.001 --> 37:02.220
- Yeah.
- You can save that for another.

37:02.263 --> 37:04.134
Especially with everything
Jen has going on,

37:04.178 --> 37:06.354
I really just wanna be here
for her.

37:06.398 --> 37:09.183
It's, like, hard now.
It's about to get harder.

37:09.227 --> 37:10.793
Well, that's the thing.
That's what we keep hearing,

37:10.837 --> 37:14.275
is that she just really needs us
to be there for her, so...

37:14.319 --> 37:16.277
In that moment,
I was kinda thinking,

37:16.321 --> 37:18.366
why don't we hurry
and take a quick trip

37:18.410 --> 37:19.802
before she goes to New York?

37:19.846 --> 37:22.065
We need to.
Where should we go?

37:22.109 --> 37:23.719
- Build on that good energy.
- Where should we go?

37:23.763 --> 37:25.417
Somewhere close,
not a long flight.

37:25.460 --> 37:28.333
- Somewhere we can just, like--
- Somewhere warm, sunshine.

37:28.376 --> 37:29.986
I was thinking Arizona.

37:30.030 --> 37:31.814
- Oh, my God. I'm in. Let's go.
- All right.

37:31.858 --> 37:33.076
I will take care of everything.

37:33.120 --> 37:35.078
I'll take care
of all the details.

37:35.122 --> 37:36.210
- Should we put a bet in?
- Okay.

37:36.254 --> 37:38.256
- Okay, girl.
- I'm gonna go all in.

37:38.299 --> 37:40.780
Oh! Let's go all in!

37:40.823 --> 37:42.303
I'm going all in
on the girls' trip.

37:42.347 --> 37:43.957
You better.

37:44.000 --> 37:46.438
14, 16.

37:46.481 --> 37:47.526
- Bet 5 more.
- I'm gonna hit.

37:47.569 --> 37:48.570
- The book says hit.
- Getting...

37:48.614 --> 37:52.008
Oh!

37:52.052 --> 37:53.793
There's no hope
for our friends!

37:53.836 --> 37:55.360
No hope.

37:56.752 --> 37:58.450
Look at her.

37:58.493 --> 37:59.755
- Yes.
- Mom, don't be trying

37:59.799 --> 38:01.104
to be mean.
No young tender for you, Mom.

38:04.586 --> 38:06.762
It looks good, right?

38:08.677 --> 38:10.723
Yes. The best thing is
the octopus.

38:10.766 --> 38:12.986
- Oh, my God.
- It's so good.

38:13.029 --> 38:14.683
- Hey.
- Hi. How are you?

38:14.727 --> 38:16.294
I wanted to say hi.

38:18.208 --> 38:21.647
Okay. Um...

38:21.690 --> 38:22.822
At some point,
I wanna talk to you

38:22.865 --> 38:24.606
if you're open to it.

38:24.650 --> 38:25.999
- Sure.
- Not tonight.

38:26.042 --> 38:29.307
You know what? You've had
two months nearly now

38:29.350 --> 38:31.961
to reach out to me and tell me
you wanna talk to me.

38:32.005 --> 38:33.746
Well, I just want you to know
I love you

38:33.789 --> 38:35.182
and I'm really, really sorry.

38:35.225 --> 38:36.705
Leave me alone.

38:36.749 --> 38:38.620
Look. Look, look. Look.

38:40.622 --> 38:42.711
Okay.

38:42.755 --> 38:46.106
Hey, Seth. How are you?

38:46.149 --> 38:47.847
- Good. How are you?
- Can I hug you?

38:47.890 --> 38:51.241
- Is it okay? You don't have to.
- No, I don't...

38:51.285 --> 38:52.852
That's huge.

38:52.895 --> 38:54.723
It was crazy, so I don't still--
trying to understand it.

38:54.767 --> 38:57.422
Yeah. I'm sorry.

38:57.465 --> 38:59.598
Meredith was devastated.

38:59.641 --> 39:01.774
I know. I know.

39:01.817 --> 39:04.907
- It was hard on me.
- Yeah, I know.

39:04.951 --> 39:08.433
You made some comments about me
that I couldn't believe either.

39:08.476 --> 39:09.825
I regret all of it.

39:09.869 --> 39:11.349
Seth, I can't even believe
I said those things.

39:11.392 --> 39:13.046
I don't feel that way
about Meredith.

39:13.089 --> 39:16.136
I don't feel that way about you.
Like, I don't. Like, I don't.

39:28.409 --> 39:30.237
Seth, I can't even believe
I said those things.

39:30.280 --> 39:31.891
I don't feel that way
about Meredith.

39:31.934 --> 39:33.066
I don't feel that way
about you.

39:33.109 --> 39:35.416
Like, I don't. Like, I don't.

39:35.460 --> 39:38.811
Seth is talking to Lisa
right now.

39:38.854 --> 39:42.902
Whatever, you know?

39:42.945 --> 39:45.861
What... we were surprised
by that, that, like...

39:45.905 --> 39:48.951
- I know.
- ...wasn't the Lisa we know.

39:48.995 --> 39:52.085
- Yeah.
- That behavior was... so hurtful.

39:52.128 --> 39:53.956
I hope you can
understand that, like,

39:54.000 --> 39:56.698
I literally haven't been able
to sleep.

39:56.742 --> 39:58.004
Like, it's been weighing on me,

39:58.047 --> 39:59.222
and, like, John's, like,
"It's gonna be okay."

39:59.266 --> 40:03.096
But, like,
it doesn't feel like it.

40:03.139 --> 40:05.272
Why is this happening here?
She's had a month.

40:05.315 --> 40:06.926
She could've texted me.
She could've texted Seth.

40:06.969 --> 40:08.580
She could've texted my children.

40:08.623 --> 40:10.277
She hasn't said anything, right?

40:10.320 --> 40:11.931
No! Like, if you wanna talk
to him, then tell us,

40:11.974 --> 40:13.541
but why are you attacking
my husband right now

40:13.585 --> 40:17.066
while we're trying to have fun
and celebrate your husband?

40:18.372 --> 40:22.158
Literally, Seth, it was like
a blind, like, rant.

40:22.202 --> 40:27.076
Have you--You know what the root
of that was?

40:27.120 --> 40:29.296
It was never before that trip.

40:29.339 --> 40:30.689
Like, I'd never thought
those things.

40:30.732 --> 40:32.517
I don't even think
those things now, but, like,

40:32.560 --> 40:34.388
on the van on the way down,
everyone's like,

40:34.432 --> 40:36.303
"She's not your friend.
Like, that's not your friend,"

40:36.346 --> 40:39.698
and then, like, just hearing it
over and over again,

40:39.741 --> 40:41.003
did that make sense?

40:41.047 --> 40:42.831
Not--None of it makes
sense to me.

40:42.875 --> 40:46.574
Like, to--to get to where
you got to,

40:46.618 --> 40:50.622
I can never imagine myself
saying something like that

40:50.665 --> 40:51.971
about someone we love.

40:52.014 --> 40:54.756
And, Seth, I understand that.

40:54.800 --> 40:58.456
Like, I don't even remember
saying those things.

40:58.499 --> 41:01.502
And I-I did feel hurt.

41:01.546 --> 41:04.331
Like, I understand Meredith
was hurting. I was hurting, too.

41:04.374 --> 41:07.247
I'm not--I'm not making excuses,

41:07.290 --> 41:10.511
but I was coming
from a place of hurt.

41:10.555 --> 41:14.384
- It just seemed so hateful.
- It was. It was hurt.

41:14.428 --> 41:16.517
I'm human, and I was hurting.
It wasn't hate.

41:16.561 --> 41:17.997
It was hurt.
I'm one of five girls,

41:18.040 --> 41:20.521
and, like, I'm a girls' girl.

41:20.565 --> 41:24.482
I have four sisters that I'm,
like, very responsible for,

41:24.525 --> 41:26.745
and, like, I have my stuff
going on, too, Seth.

41:26.788 --> 41:28.660
Nobody knows what goes on
for me.

41:28.703 --> 41:31.445
Nobody asked me,
and then I'm trying to, like,

41:31.489 --> 41:32.838
be there for others.

41:32.881 --> 41:35.449
I've never talked badly
about Meredith to anyone.

41:37.973 --> 41:39.758
There's not one person
in this friend group

41:39.801 --> 41:42.456
that can say I've ever said
anything about her.

41:42.500 --> 41:43.805
The rant was...

41:43.849 --> 41:46.895
I know, but I thought I was
in a private space

41:46.939 --> 41:50.290
just, like, hurting.

41:50.333 --> 41:52.205
It wasn't meant for anybody else
to hear.

41:52.248 --> 41:59.125
And, like, I don't expect you
to, like, like, forgive.

41:59.168 --> 42:02.737
She's hurt more than me,
and rightfully so.

42:02.781 --> 42:06.872
It's hard right now, so, like,
we'll just keep moving forward.

42:06.915 --> 42:08.874
Thanks for listening to me.

42:12.051 --> 42:13.705
Do I have a problem
saying I'm sorry? Never.

42:13.748 --> 42:16.229
Do I have a problem
taking accountability

42:16.272 --> 42:18.492
for my actions or my words?
Not at all.

42:18.536 --> 42:20.407
But at some point,
if it's not being heard,

42:20.450 --> 42:23.279
and the apology
isn't being accepted,

42:23.323 --> 42:26.369
there's nothing more I can do.
I have to move on.

42:26.413 --> 42:30.417
- Do you care if we leave?
- You okay?

42:30.460 --> 42:33.246
- What was she saying?
- I wasn't ready for it.

42:33.289 --> 42:36.118
- Why did you even go there?
- What was I gonna do?

42:36.162 --> 42:38.556
I would say,
"It's not the time and place."

42:40.209 --> 42:44.257
The bad news is she doesn't--
She seems to be excusing it

42:44.300 --> 42:46.825
and not taking accountability
for it.

42:46.868 --> 42:50.393
Is it an apology when
you're excusing the behavior?

42:50.437 --> 42:51.525
No.

42:51.569 --> 42:53.048
